    "# Project 5.2 – Scenario Analysis and Business Insights\n",
    "\n",
    "This project extends the optimized machine learning models developed in Project 4.2. The purpose of this analysis is to evaluate how the neural network model responds to realistic changes in patient characteristics and determine how those changes influence heart disease risk predictions.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2c692292",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Scenario Development\n",
    "\n",
    "### Scenario 1 – Aging Population\n",
    "**Assumption:** Average patient age increases by 10 years.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rationale:** Age is a major risk factor for heart disease.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Scenario 2 – Improved Cholesterol Management\n",
    "**Assumption:** Cholesterol levels decrease by 20%.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rationale:** Lower cholesterol is associated with improved cardiovascular health.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Scenario 3 – Improved Cardiovascular Fitness\n",
    "**Assumption:** Maximum heart rate (thalch) increases by 10% while oldpeak decreases by 20%.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rationale:** Simulates a healthier and more physically active population.\n"
   ]
